text: Sphingomonas insulae is a Gram-negative, rod-shaped and motile bacteria from the genus of Sphingomonas which has been isolated from soil in Dokdo in Korea.Deutsche Sammlung von Mikroorganismen und Zellkulturen UniProt == Further reading == * < == References == ==External links== *Type strain of Sphingomonas insulae at BacDive - the Bacterial Diversity Metadatabase insulae Category:Bacteria described in 2008
